positions.title: Software Engineer in Test
positions.description:
**Job Summary**

The Maps team is seeking a seasoned, highly technical Automation Engineer with strong computer science and software experience to architect and develop test automation frameworks and tools. You will be building software to support the entire maps eval team to expedite, stabiles and innovate the maps client test processes within the organization. You will be responsible for defining and cultivating the automation and test standards. This includes working closely with partner teams and stakeholders to collect requirements and building feedback pipelines to facilitate automation and testing. We are looking for critical thinkers who enjoy innovating and solving complex, highly visible and impactful challenges. This position requires a self-motivated individual with strong problem solving skills who can contribute in a dynamic team environment.

**Key Qualifications**
- Creative thinker and a strong problem solver.
- Excellent knowledge of test methodologies.
- Python and Java programming skills are strongly desired.
- Hands-on experience with automation framework design and implementation.
- Strong computer science fundamentals
- Experience building high-performance test applications
- 7 or more years of experience
